s, United Kingdom":"Llandyssiliogogo, Cardiganshire, Wales, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"ferch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Ferg  . Compare   Verch  .","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förtsch</b> (see   Foertsch  ).","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förch</b> (see   Foerch  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Ferg","meanings":["German: occupational name for a ferryman, Middle High German <i>verje</i>, <i>verge</i>."]}]},{"name":"Llywelyn","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Welsh: variant of   Llewellyn  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Llewellyn","meanings":["Welsh: from the personal name <i>Llywelyn</i>, derived from British Celtic <i>Lugubelinos</i>, itself from the divine name <i>Lugus</i> + an uncertain second element often used alone as a name. Through association with <i>llew</i> ‘lion’, it was altered to <i>Llewelyn</i>. This was the name of two princes of north Wales who held the Normans at bay for many years in the 13th century. Etymologically speaking, the form with a fourth <i>-l-</i> is an error, not found as an original Welsh name, but this is now much the most common spelling in the US."]}]},{"name":"Lleucu","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Lucia</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1352858,"age":14,"year":"1519","julianDay":2275863,"description":"Charles I of Spain became Emperor Charles V of the Holy Roman Empire.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Lleucu ferch Llywelyn was born about 1505, in Llandyssiliogogo, Cardiganshire, Wales, United Kingdom, her father, Llewelyn ap Dafydd, was 41 and her mother, Margaret Thomas, was 10. She married Harry ap Rhys in 1525, in Abergwili, Carmarthenshire, Wales, United Kingdom. They were the pa